SUMMARY:How to get your start in business journalism
DESCRIPTION:SABEW Canada and Shared Bylines are teaming up at last! Join us for a panel on how to get your start in business journalism\, sponsored by Fidelity Investments Canada. \nWe’re celebrating the upcoming sixth year of the Shared Bylines scholarship and mentorship program for BIPOC student journalists\, as well as the new Fidelity-Shared Bylines Business Scholarship\, with a panel and social event on April 14th at the Pilot. \nHosted by SABEW CA co-chair Laura Hensley\, the panel will hear from Ana Pereira\, Curtis Heinzl and Meera Raman who will chat about what it’s like being an early-career business journalist\, give advice on getting started (whether that’s choosing the right internship\, pitching the right story or picking up the right set of skills) and hopefully inspire you – whether you’re a student\, an early-career reporter or a more experienced journalist looking to broaden your horizons. \nRegister for the event
URL:https://sabew.org/event/how-to-get-your-start-in-business-journalism/
LOCATION:The Pilot\, 22 Cumberland Street\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M4W 1J5\, Canada
CATEGORIES:SABEW Canada
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://sabew.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/654159749_18093067496515714_4764368129513197403_n.jpg
END:VEVENT
